==English==
===Etymology===
[[umpty]] (colloquial name for the dash "&mdash;" in Morse code) + ''teen'', by analogy with the cardinal numbers from [[thirteen]] to [[nineteen]].

===Adjective===
{{wikipedia}}
'''umpteen'''

An unknown number, X, where X is usually exceedingly large
#:''She's taking umpteen friends with her to the party.''

====Translations====
*Spanish: una [[multitud]] de; un [[montón]] de
*Swedish: [[femtioelva]]

